short_description: S4/HANA - Multiple errors
description:
What were you trying to do when the issue happened? I was trying to order from the catalog app in S4.  I had reached the Purchase Request page after the system transferred me from the catalog app.
 
What transaction code or Fiori app were you using? I was using the "Creata Purchase Requistion" app tile that I added to my Fiori dashboard.

What error message did you receive (if any)?  the error message I received was a "back-end error"

Are other users experiencing the same issue?  I don't know if anyone else is having this issue.
 
Have you done this task successfully before in S/4, or is this your first attempt?  I have been unable to get any catalog or purchase requistion requests through the entire process so far.  there have been multiple problems with the system.
 
Can you reproduce the issue? If yes, what are the steps?  I have attempted the process multiple times.  This is the first time I have gotten this far in the process without other issues first.  I forwarded my previous attempts to other departments for assistance.  The steps are:
1.I log into S4 Fiori to reach my dashboard
2.I click on the PR tile which pulls up the initial PR request page.  I click on the catalog icon and I am taken to the catalog page.
3.In this particular incidence I choose Runco catalog and I am redirected to the Runco catalog as normal
4.When i search for an item via part number I get the correct item with price.  I put that item in my cart.
-However if I search for another item, the item comes up but I am not given a price
-Instead the Runco catalog tells me that I must login into my account to see a price.  I don't have a login
-In this particular incident I choose only one item.  
-When I tried to submit my cart I was redirected to the Purchase Requistion page.
-The Material column on the PR page was blank as usual.
-I tried to search for the correct material category and that is when I got the "back-end error" message.

What is the document number, user ID, or material number (if applicable)?

Did you try clearing your browser cache or switching to another browser (for Fiori)? Troubling shooting so far:
Restarted and updated my laptop
I don't have access to Google Chrome on this laptop, it is due for an upgrade, but none were available
I tried to launch Chrome but it asks for a log in and I am not aware of having a log in

Is this urgent or time-sensitive? What's the business impact?  Yes, this urgent, we are running out of several critical supplies, and I need to be able to order them as soon as possible.

short_description: This request is to make a copy of the Project Costs: Plan/Actual/Commit/RemainingPlanned/Assigned report and hard code the inclusion of cost element 65901000
description:
This request is to make a copy of the Project Costs: Plan/Actual/Commit/RemainingPlanned/Assigned report and hard code the inclusion of cost element 65901000 and the filtering out of 65901001 in a custom transaction named ZPS03.  Tile information is attached. 

As project actuals were loaded into S4, we noticed that the numbers were not showing up on the Project Costs: Plan/Actual/Commit/RemainingPlanned/Assigned report in S4.  Investigation into this led us to see  that since both the credit and the debit were applied to the WBS element, they are netting to 0.  I spoke with our Reply consultant and he determined there is no way to make criteria changes on a standard SAP report which is why we are requesting a custom report.

short_description: VL01N - Outbound Delivery without Order Reference
description:
Custom Zcode for LTL shipments of parts to get sent out from our storehouses to repair shops and also waste disposal, ZSCDTRK, is no longer in S4.  We worked with Amy Madden to replace this with "Create Outbound Delivery Without Order Reference"

We have 4 materials we need to ship out using the ZSCDTRK replacement, Create Outbound Delivery Without Order Reference.  When we are filling out the Ship-to-party for materials, we are sending them out to suppliers to repair.  But the only things selectable are customers, no suppliers (the supplier are the ones that repair parts and receive waste disposal shipments).  

The main thing we need to be able to do is the following:
Create a delivery with a BOL print out for the shipment.  Enter weights/route/etc.  Use E2Open to tender a truck to pick up the load from any site.  Pack and PGI when the truck arrives.  For repaired parts, tender truck to deliver load back to plant and perform a goods receipt to place back in stock.   

I recommend we update the Business Partner Configuration for a handful of suppliers to the sales areas.   They would be set up as both Suppliers and Customers.

short_description: Weights are transmitting in tons and needs to be pounds, otherwise billing will fail in BDS.

Hasan, i need more information on this, because currently we are sending only weight in TON.

07-10-2025 11:47:51 - Saverio Tranquilli (Work notes)
Assigned to Kedar. The logic in CPI hasn't changed and is driven by S/4.

Weights are transmitting in tons and needs to be pounds, otherwise billing will fail. I checked a few of the payloads we've been getting in CPIsome are using LB as the unit of weight, and others are using TON. We don't need to make any changes in CPI since the logic comes from S/4. If S/4 sends LB, we send LB to Bourque; if it sends TON, we send TON to BDS. @Tingrikar, Kedar will advise if any changes can be made in S/4 to handle this.



Also, for shipments manually billed, is there a way to not transit again, suppress output to BDS? This will need to be addressed in S/4. @Tingrikar, Kedar, please advise.

short_description: the line item is greyed out when I try to PGI 2 truck's from Canal #80004440 & 80004441 (snippet attached)
description: the line item is greyed out when I try to PGI 2 truck's from Canal #80004440 & 80004441 (snippet attached)

I wanted to raise a control concern regarding the current workflow for Debit and Credit Memos in the system.  I believe it presents a potential audit risk, so please see details and thoughts below:
Issue:
Debit and Credit Memo tiles allow users to recall submissions for approval.
Once recalled, users enter change mode, enabling them to create billing documents without re-approval.
This bypasses the required independent review and approval, creating an audit compliance risk.
Audit Concern:
To meet requirements, all debits and credits are to be reviewed and released by someone other than the creator.
The current process in S/4 allows for self-approval, which violates segregation of duties.
Recommendation:
Default to a billing block on all debit and credit memos.
Ensure the billing block cannot be removed by the document creator.
Essentially, reinstate the control that existed in ECC, which satisfied audit requirements.

short_description: Master Data Migration issue.   Not all OA migrated, and some need to be on Source lists.
description:
Storeroom PR 's are generating PO's against catalog outline agreements instead of HIBE OA's. See PO 4500005665 this PO was issued against a catalog outline agreement. How did this happen? The PO should not have flipped since the material is not sourced. PO 4500005665, material 10086707, PR 3000009737, incorrect OA listed on PO is 4600000021

SAP does sourcing in a hierarchy.  Quota, then Source List, then contract, then PIR.  In this case the OA for HIBE was not migrated, but the CAT contract was.  There was no Source list since the HIBE specific contract was not migrated.  On the sourcing, it fell to the CAT OA.

As a result, the system is defaulting to plant code 1010 (which is tied to the account here: https://shop.equallevel.com/advansix/accounts/1673) and assigned the account's associated "Amines Business" group, for all incoming users. I've included examples of some of the most recent punchout data we've received from your system for various users.

short_description: S4 Customer ZIP Code Formats Not Compatible with BDS Rate Server - BDS Rate Server will only accept 5 digit zip codes - Modify Interface to only send 5 digits
description:
Rail routes will not pull in, customer ship to address's in S4 are 5 digits plus a dash and 4 additional digits. We will need a mass update for all rail ship to's to only note a 5 digit zip code. High priority.  Note this issue was originally opened under INC0119007 which was closed when the issue was not resolved yet.  , Rate Server only recognizes 5 digit code of ship to.  When SAP ship to with more than five digits is passed on delivery BOL to Railtrac, this stop the process no waybill generated as Rate Server does not recognize. Example attached, delivery BOL passed, stop process, waybill did not generate, so shipment is now delayed.

Recommend we modify the interface to only send the first 5 zip code digits to rate server as modifying the customer master would be impacted by a future MDG deployments

short_description: Escalating this issue to get these process orders and HUs fixed to the correct quantity. This is grossly understating the tanker weights (and is keeping us from
description:
Escalating this issue to get these process orders and HUs fixed to the correct quantity. This is grossly understating the tanker weights (and is keeping us from assigning to deliveries and/or offloading). I want to make sure someone is aware and working on this issue, and to also find out how you all can avoid this for any other, upcoming tanker lots.
 
There are (3) H8202NLB-TNK lots that have process orders and HUs showing ~47 lbs instead of ~47k lbs. It looks like someone is putting a decimal in instead of a comma
Ive outlined the batch# / Process order# / HU#s for these 3 that Ive found thus far. These need to be fixed.
 
Please work on these to resolve the issues. We will need these fixed to either assign to upcoming tanker deliveries to customers -or- set up to be offloaded. But need the correct quantities in S4 inventory to do so.
 
	Batch# 0000001837  Process order# 1004555  HU# 212001090000370391   (from 8/22)
	Batch# 0000001838  Process order# 1004556  HU# 212001090000370711    (from 8/22)

short_description: CoAs for flake lactam printing out in the HPW QA Lab need several corrections
description: The CoAs for flake lactam printing out in the HPW QA Lab need several corrections.  I have marked up the multiple issues on the CoA and am also attaching a corrected CoA for example/comparison.  These CoAs do NOT need to be released to customers until these corrections have been made please.   1.  The analysis date is printing incorrect on all of the CoAs.  It should be the date data was entered into LabVantage.  2. The expiration date is 1 year + 1 day, not just 1 year from manufacture date. 3.  Product:  10071192 Caprolactam FLAKES mechant - bags.  4. The color analysis/data is completely missing from the CoA being sent to customers at the moment.  5.  Assay should NOT be on this CoA.  6.  FE needs to be Iron (Fe) under component and the units are PPM (capitalized).  7.  Volatile Base (NH3) does not need decimal places for specs and we report to tenth not hundreths, and units are MEQ/KG. 8. Units for volatile base (meq/kg) should actually say MEQ/KG since it's in the title. 9.  Water units are WT/WT PERC not PERCENT.  10.  Take the quotation marks off of the comments section writing.
